# CSS: Styling Your Web Page

CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) makes HTML look good.

## Adding CSS to HTML

### Method 1: Inside a <style> tag
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        h1 {
            color: blue;
        }

        p {
            color: gray;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>My Website</h1>
    <p>This is styled!</p>
</body>
</html>
```

### Method 2: External CSS File

**index.html:**
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>My Website</h1>
</body>
</html>
```

**style.css:**
```css
body {
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
}
```

## Common CSS Properties

```css
/* Colors */
color: blue;              /* Text color */
background-color: yellow; /* Background color */

/* Fonts */
font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
font-size: 18px;
font-weight: bold;

/* Spacing */
margin: 20px;     /* Outside spacing */
padding: 10px;    /* Inside spacing */

/* Size */
width: 200px;
height: 100px;

/* Borders */
border: 2px solid black;
border-radius: 5px;

/* Text alignment */
text-align: center;
```

## Classes and IDs

Apply styles to specific elements:

```html
<style>
    .highlight {
        background-color: yellow;
    }

    #main-title {
        color: darkblue;
        font-size: 32px;
    }
</style>

<h1 id="main-title">Welcome</h1>
<p class="highlight">This is highlighted</p>
<p class="highlight">This is also highlighted</p>
```

# Routes in Flask

Routes map URLs to Python functions.

## Multiple Routes

```python
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return "<h1>Home Page</h1>"

@app.route("/about")
def about():
    return "<h1>About Us</h1>"

@app.route("/contact")
def contact():
    return "<h1>Contact Page</h1>"

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)
```

Now you have:
- `http://localhost:5000/` - Shows Home Page
- `http://localhost:5000/about` - Shows About Us
- `http://localhost:5000/contact` - Shows Contact Page

## Dynamic Routes (Variable URLs)

Catch values from the URL:

```python
@app.route("/user/<name>")
def greet_user(name):
    return f"<h1>Hello, {name}!</h1>"
```

Now:
- `http://localhost:5000/user/alice` - Shows: Hello, alice!
- `http://localhost:5000/user/bob` - Shows: Hello, bob!

## URL with Multiple Variables

```python
@app.route("/post/<int:post_id>")
def show_post(post_id):
    return f"<h1>Post #{post_id}</h1>"

@app.route("/user/<name>/<int:age>")
def user_info(name, age):
    return f"<p>{name} is {age} years old</p>"
```
